<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A narrow endemic restricted to seasonally very arid spiny bushland on descent to Pampa Negra in Vallegrande Province in Bolivia between 1650 and 1800 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">BOLIVIA. Santa Cruz</emphasis>
: Vallegrande, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">J.R.I. Wood et al.</emphasis>
28443 (LPB, OXF, USZ).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A scrambling or decumbent species with dimorphic leaves and stems which distinctly proliferate.</paragraph>
